                            <handNote>Black letters against white background.
The inscription is written entirely in uppercase. Lines are ruled top and bottom. Accents and breathings non systematic. The end of the text is marked with a middle dot.
The inscription is clear, legible and consists of bold letters. From the middle and onwards of the text, the words are thinner and slightly compressed for space reasons.
At the beginning of the inscription there are ligatures of the letters ΟΥ, ΝΗ. The letters Ε and Ω form inside them something like small spheres.
Very good preservation condition. <height unit="cm">? cm</height>
