            <div type="translation" source="#MangoHawkinsBoyd1990">
                <p>“Thus saith the Lord: Behold, I will open your graves and bring you up, out of your graves”. Translation by Mango, Hawkins, Boys 1990, 85.</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text comes from Ezekiel’s prophecy (Ezek. 37:12) and refers to the Resurrection’s scene on the south wall. 
The text starts with a decorative cross. Specifically, is depicted a cross with rays.</p>
